---

ARCHITECTURAL GOAL

Current salvage classification is derived from simple rule checks.

FORMAT-07 introduces graph-aware reasoning using surviving verified records.

Recovered information is treated as nodes and relationships.

Example conceptual model:

nodes
- block
- extent
- file_manifest
- path_checkpoint

edges
- block -> extent
- extent -> file_manifest
- file_manifest -> path_checkpoint

Salvage builds a surviving verified graph and classifies recovery strength from connected components.

---

NEW RECOVERY CLASSES

Replace coarse classification with the following ordered hierarchy.

1 FULL_NAMED_VERIFIED

Definition
All blocks verified
file manifest verified
path mapping verified

Meaning
Complete recovery including original path and name.

2 FULL_ANONYMOUS_VERIFIED

Definition
All blocks verified
file manifest verified
path mapping missing or rejected

Meaning
Complete file recovered but without trusted filename.

3 PARTIAL_ORDERED_VERIFIED

Definition
Subset of blocks verified
ordering provable from manifest or extents

Meaning
Recoverable file fragment with known order.

4 PARTIAL_UNORDERED_VERIFIED

Definition
Subset of blocks verified
ordering cannot be proven

Meaning
Data fragments recovered but sequence uncertain.

5 ORPHAN_EVIDENCE_ONLY

Definition
Verified blocks exist
no provable file grouping

Meaning
Forensic evidence but no file reconstruction.

6 NO_VERIFIED_EVIDENCE

Definition
No blocks pass verification.

Meaning
Archive unrecoverable.

---

SALVAGE GRAPH CONSTRUCTION

Inputs

verified_blocks
verified_extents
verified_file_manifests
verified_path_records

Graph build rules

block node created for each verified payload block

extent node created when extent record survives

file_manifest node created when manifest record survives

path node created when path checkpoint survives

Edges

block -> extent
extent -> file_manifest
file_manifest -> path

Only edges backed by verified records are allowed.

Conflicting metadata must be rejected.

---

CLASSIFICATION ALGORITHM

Pseudo logic

build_verified_graph()

group connected components by file_manifest

for each component

    block_count = verified blocks
    expected_count = manifest block count if known
    has_manifest = manifest node present
    has_path = path node present
    ordering_known = extent sequence verified

    if has_manifest AND block_count == expected_count AND has_path
        FULL_NAMED_VERIFIED

    else if has_manifest AND block_count == expected_count
        FULL_ANONYMOUS_VERIFIED

    else if block_count > 0 AND ordering_known
        PARTIAL_ORDERED_VERIFIED

    else if block_count > 0
        PARTIAL_UNORDERED_VERIFIED

    else
        ORPHAN_EVIDENCE_ONLY

